node.text:
To defeat an enemy against humanity, it takes all of us. June 6, 1944, also known as D-Day, was a crucial moment in the second World War. It took strategy, strength, and most of all, selflessness to achieve victory, but none of it could have come without sacrifice. We remember D-Day and the men who gave it their all for a better world tomorrow.

node.text:
U.S. Air Force Special Warfare SSgt Brittany and SSgt Wayne train with @ufc Strawweight @carlaesparza1 at the @ufcpi in Las Vegas, NV. All three of them test their physical and mental strengths as they complete the Eyes on the Prize workout. 
 
Head to the link in bio to learn more about the intensive training Special Warfare Airmen go through. @usafspecwarrecruiting

Disclaimer: Video was shot prior to the COVID-19 pandemic.

Happy #PresidentsDay from the ones keeping the President on the move! Here are some fun facts about the world’s fanciest, most functional ride: Air Force One. 
 
✈️ Air Force One is not just one plane—it’s a term used for any @usairforce aircraft carrying the President. 
✈️ Because the President may need to travel to the furthest locations at any given time, Air Force One is capable of refueling midair giving it unlimited range.
✈️ Air Force One is a technological marvel! These aircraft are equipped with advanced secure communications equipment, allowing the aircraft to function as a mobile command center in the event of an emergency.
✈️ Can you say spacious? Air Force One has over 4,000 square feet of floor space on three levels, including an extensive suite for the President, a conference room, a medical suite that can function as an operating room, and two food preparation galleys that can feed 100 people at a time.

Talk about weathering the storm ⛈️
 
The @af_reserve_hurricane_hunters are the only @deptofdefense unit to actually fly into hurricanes in order to gather weather data. 
 
Hurricane Hunters help prevent the aftermath of natural disasters by sharing their data from inside the storm with the National Hurricane Center. Thanks to the Hurricane Hunters, the National Hurricane Center can lessen storm impacts by giving community members enough time and details to properly prepare. Umbrella, anyone? ☂️

Diversity makes us stronger, take MSgt Shale Norwitz’s word for it.

MSgt Shale Norwitz’s differences, though not as visible, make him a better Airman. As an Airman on the autism spectrum, MSgt Norwitz finds his neurodiversity to be an asset, not an obstacle. 

“I’m on the [autism] spectrum and that makes me good at being a strategic thinker, and contributes to my innovation,” Norwitz said. “The final step is to accept [being autistic]. That is how we rise [from negative stereotypes]. If we can learn and educate ourselves, we can elevate to a position of acceptance.”
